<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="16" pageNumber="489" type="mainText">Remarks: This is a dull black ant of moderate size, which is commonly found throughout open forest in tropical Africa and extends to southern Arabia (Collingwood 1985). Hairs are present on the ventral head and on the vertex. Size variation in workers is low, the species appears monomorphic. In contrast, many other species of the genus (including the two others present on Socotra) show extensive size variation and allometric effects, making small and large workers appear very different.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
